From: nbl-sdk <noreply@example.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] config: recognize SW64 Linux targets

Teach GNU Readline's bundled config.sub about the SW64 CPU name so its
configure script accepts the SDK's sw_64-linux-musl target.

---
 support/config.sub | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/support/config.sub b/support/config.sub
--- a/support/config.sub
+++ b/support/config.sub
@@ -1429,6 +1429,7 @@ case $cpu in
 			| sparcv9b \
 			| sparcv9v \
 			| spu \
+			| sw_64 \
 			| sv1 \
 			| sx* \
 			| tahoe \
-- 
2.47.3
